# Tailwind CSS Styling Guidelines

## Color Palette
- **Primary**: Use slate colors (slate-900, slate-800, slate-300) for backgrounds and text
- **Accent**: Use blue, purple, and emerald gradients for highlights and buttons
- **Semantic**: Use red for errors, green for success, yellow for warnings

## Layout & Spacing
- Use consistent spacing scale (4, 6, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24)
- Implement responsive design with mobile-first approach
- Use container classes for content width management
- Apply proper padding and margins for visual hierarchy

## Component Styling
- Use backdrop-blur and border effects for modern glass-morphism
- Implement gradient backgrounds for visual appeal
- Use rounded corners consistently (rounded-xl, rounded-2xl)
- Apply proper shadows for depth (shadow-2xl, shadow-lg)

## Animation & Transitions
- Use Tailwind's animation utilities (animate-float, animate-fade-in)
- Implement smooth transitions (transition-all duration-300)
- Use transform utilities for hover effects
- Apply proper animation delays for staggered effects

## Responsive Design
- Use responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Implement proper breakpoint strategies
- Ensure mobile-friendly touch targets
- Use flexbox and grid for responsive layouts

## Accessibility
- Maintain proper color contrast ratios
- Use semantic HTML with proper ARIA labels
- Implement focus states for keyboard navigation
- Ensure text readability across all screen sizes
